      <div class="msgContentFrame">I've noticed that on FFXIPro achievements, although not a complete database, shows that thaumaturgy has the least amount of level 50s. All other classes have pretty much dozens, where as thaumaturges only have 2 listed level 50s. <br /> <br />Is there a reason for this? I find it weird that there are so, so many conjurers compared to thaumaturges. In practice I have never felt like a third wheel in a party or felt that I level slower, in fact I feel like I have a lot more ways to skill up compared to conjurers; whom seem to nearly all rely completely on healing SP. <br /> <br />Is it the name? Is it our conal AoE's? What's the deal, why are we so under represented?</div>
