      <div class="msgContentFrame">IMHO  (I have CON 21 and THM 18 atm)  <br /> <br />CON has more burst for sure, and if you pick the weak element of the mobs you are grinding you do massive damage. <br /> <br />THM honestly has way more skill synergy. If you play it right :D  Add some CON skills that add damage (profundity etc) and voila! <br /> <br />PS i craft a lot, so I have high Fire &amp; Wind &amp; Lightning affinity. This is 100% of Astral damage. So even when I roll as a THM I use Radiance, higher CD sure, but with Banish's debuff (and depending on the affinity of your staff/scepter) you can pull some 300+ Radiance moves. <br /> <br />Deeper in to the jobs, I see more in CON I like TBH, and maybe i will switch to Umbral affinity to make more use of THM's strengths. I think astral/umbral might come ahead when there isn't a weak element to prey upon.   <br /> <br />My two cents, seem to roll as CON more lately ... but that is just because I had to start picking one job to focus on lol. THM has weaker def gear (and was a lower stat cap) so I slid it to the back burner for awhile. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 16th 2010  3:51pm by SpelunkerOne </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1459262.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
